    "import warnings\n",
    "import iris\n",
    "\n",

    "\n",
    "with warnings.catch_warnings():\n",
    "    warnings.simplefilter(\"ignore\")\n",
    "    cubes = iris.load_raw(url)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-10-23T07:00:07.802336Z",

     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-10-23T07:00:09.957086Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-10-23T07:00:09.956515Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "salt = cubes.extract_cube(\"sea_water_practical_salinity\")[-1, ...]  # Last time step.\n",
    "\n",
    "lon = salt.coord(axis=\"X\").points\n",
    "lat = salt.coord(axis=\"Y\").points"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,

    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-10-23T07:00:09.959479Z",

     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-10-23T07:00:14.564662Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "p = salt.coord(\"sea_surface_height_above_reference_ellipsoid\").points\n",
    "q = salt.data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,

     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-10-23T07:00:14.567307Z",

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from ciso import zslice\n",
    "\n",
    "p0 = -250\n",
    "\n",
    "isoslice = zslice(q.astype(np.float64), p, p0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,

    "execution": {

   "source": [
    "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from cartopy.io import shapereader\n",
    "from cartopy.mpl.gridliner import LATITUDE_FORMATTER, LONGITUDE_FORMATTER\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "extent = [lon.min(), lon.max(), lat.min(), lat.max()]\n",
    "\n",
    "def make_map(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree()):\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 13), subplot_kw=dict(projection=projection))\n",
    "    gl = ax.gridlines(draw_labels=True)\n",
    "    gl.right_labels = gl.top_labels = False\n",
    "    gl.xformatter = LONGITUDE_FORMATTER\n",
    "    gl.yformatter = LATITUDE_FORMATTER\n",
    "    ax.set_extent(extent)\n",
    "    ax.coastlines(\"50m\")\n",
    "    return fig, ax"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-10-23T07:00:14.883549Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-10-23T07:00:14.883277Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-10-23T07:00:15.211446Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-10-23T07:00:15.210918Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy.ma as ma\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = make_map()\n",
    "\n",
    "cs = ax.pcolormesh(lon, lat, ma.masked_invalid(isoslice))\n",
    "\n",
    "kw = {\"shrink\": 0.5, \"orientation\": \"vertical\", \"extend\": \"both\"}\n",
    "cbar = fig.colorbar(cs, **kw)"
   ]
  }
